abstract: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
snippet: The enormous defense bill, one of the most expensive in the nation’s history, contains a litany of bipartisan rebukes to Russia, Turkey and China.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate on Tuesday voted overwhelmingly to pass a bipartisan $738 billion defense policy bill, sending President Trump one of the most expensive military measures in the nation’s history and one that he has championed as a critical priority.

abstract: In a year of many dispiriting headlines, Fixes still found the better angels of human nature at work.
snippet: In a year of many dispiriting headlines, Fixes still found the better angels of human nature at work.
lead_paragraph: O.K., so Time magazine has Greta Thunberg. But many other individuals also changed the world for the better in 2019. Here, for a second year, is a list of five whose contributions Fixes wrote about.

abstract: ABBA's Bjorn Ulvaeus has gifted books to high school students across Sweden to try to stem the flow of fake news.
snippet: ABBA's Bjorn Ulvaeus has gifted books to high school students across Sweden to try to stem the flow of fake news.
lead_paragraph: STOCKHOLM — ABBA's Bjorn Ulvaeus has gifted books to high school students across Sweden to try to stem the flow of fake news.
headline_main: ABBA's Bjorn Sends Sweden's Students SOS on Fake News
headline_print_headline: ABBA's Bjorn Sends Sweden's Students SOS on Fake News

abstract: A small group of President Donald Trump's fiercest conservative critics, including the husband of the president's own chief adviser, is launching a super PAC designed to fight Trump's reelection and punish congressional Republicans deemed his “enablers."
snippet: A small group of President Donald Trump's fiercest conservative critics, including the husband of the president's own chief adviser, is launching a super PAC designed to fight Trump's reelection and punish congressional Republicans deemed his “ena...
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — A small group of President Donald Trump's fiercest conservative critics, including the husband of the president's own chief adviser, is launching a super PAC designed to fight Trump's reelection and punish congressional Republicans deemed his “enablers."
headline_main: Trump Conservative Critics Launch PAC to Fight Reelection
headline_print_headline: Trump Conservative Critics Launch PAC to Fight Reelection

headline_main: Jarring Billboards’ Goal: To Prevent Pedestrian Deaths

abstract: Edbert Aquino is a national handwriting champion from New Jersey, where a lawmaker wants all public schools to teach the skill again.
snippet: Edbert Aquino is a national handwriting champion from New Jersey, where a lawmaker wants all public schools to teach the skill again.
lead_paragraph: A fifth grader in New Jersey is a master of curlicues and connecting loops. His technique is so good he was named a state and national champion of a dying art: cursive writing, a skill that once seemed destined to go the way of the typewriter.

abstract: Why did my sweet 5-year-old become so stormy when she started kindergarten?
snippet: Why did my sweet 5-year-old become so stormy when she started kindergarten?
lead_paragraph: My 5-year-old daughter had been called the Buddha baby. Not by me, but by many a stranger and friend — reliable observers. But when she starts kindergarten, she becomes, abruptly, no longer the Buddha baby. At night, she weeps and begs not to go to school. In the morning, the same. She is sad but also enraged. She kicks me for not having a banana. She punches me in the stomach for not being able to find her bumpy red ball. She says repeatedly that she is leaving to find a new family.

abstract: A lesson worth remembering: “Don’t predict impeachment politics.”
snippet: A lesson worth remembering: “Don’t predict impeachment politics.”
lead_paragraph: A veteran political reporter who covered the Clinton impeachment offered me some good advice this afternoon: “Don’t predict impeachment politics.”

abstract: Michael R. Bloomberg is showing what a virtually bottomless advertising budget can do by buying his way into the hottest political conversations of the moment.
snippet: Michael R. Bloomberg is showing what a virtually bottomless advertising budget can do by buying his way into the hottest political conversations of the moment.
lead_paragraph: Type the word “impeachment” into Google, and odds are the first search result won’t offer a news report on the latest developments in Washington.

abstract: My 91-year-old father-in-law happily eats plant-based hamburgers. That gives me a little more hope for the environment.
snippet: My 91-year-old father-in-law happily eats plant-based hamburgers. That gives me a little more hope for the environment.
lead_paragraph: NASHVILLE — Here is how my father-in-law now begins every meal at our house: He asks the blessing, unfolds his napkin and prepares to tuck in. Then he pauses, his fork still in the air, and asks, “Is this real meat?”
